        <span class="kicker">Case study</span>
        <h1 class="mt14">From “looks good” to “feels true” — Tuscany villa transformation.</h1>
        <p class="lead mt14">
          A strong example of what happens when brand clarity becomes the lens for everything you create.
        </p>

        <div class="grid-2 mt24">
          <div class="card">
            <h2>Before</h2>
            <ul class="list">
              <li>Renting seasonally through Booking.com</li>
              <li>~12k followers</li>
              <li>Minimal direct leads</li>
              <li>No retreat strategy</li>
              <li>Content looked good — but didn’t reflect who they truly were</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h2>After</h2>
            <ul class="list">
              <li>50k engaged followers</li>
              <li>4 retreats per year</li>
              <li>A clear lead generation system</li>
              <li>100 hot leads</li>
              <li>20% increase in OTA performance — with less dependency on them</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt24">
          <h2>The most important outcome</h2>
          <blockquote class="quote mt14">
            <p>Guests arrived already aligned with the experience.</p>
            <small>That’s what clarity does: it builds trust before the first message, before the first booking, before arrival.</small>
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt24">
          <h2>What made the difference</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            We didn’t chase trends. We clarified identity first — then translated it into storytelling. That’s why it converted.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-3 mt14">
            <div class="card soft">
              <h3>Diagnosis</h3>
              <p class="small m0">Where trust broke down and where messaging was generic.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card soft">
              <h3>Alignment</h3>
              <p class="small m0">A coherent voice that matched the real experience.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card soft">
              <h3>Expression</h3>
              <p class="small m0">Content that sounded like them — so the right guests self-selected.</p>
